====================================================================================================
# Whitespace in Strings

Whitespace is handled differently in different types of string notation, especially the ones that don't have a closing quotation mark.

@string/whitespace
====================================================================================================
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Leading and trailing whitespace is preserved, as it obviously should be.

"  abc  "

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

<String value="  abc  "/>

====================================================================================================
In one-liner strings without a closing quotation mark, trailing whitespace is trimmed.

@string/one-liner/whitespace
====================================================================================================
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Trim trailing whitespace

"abc    

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

<String value="abc"/>

====================================================================================================
In indented strings without a closing quotation mark, trailing whitespace (including newlines) is trimmed.

@string/indented/whitespace
====================================================================================================
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Leading whitespace preserved

"

    abc

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

<String value="
abc"/>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Trailing newlines not preserved

"
    abc



- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

<String value="abc"/>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"
    abc

1

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

<String value="abc"/>
<Integer value="1"/>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Leading whitespace after the indentation is preserved

"
        abc
     d
       e

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

<String value="    abc
 d
   e"/>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Even a full indent after the block indentation is preserved.

"
    A
        B

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

<String value="A
    B"/>

====================================================================================================
In indented strings with a closing quotation mark, trailing newlines are preserved but spaces and tabs on those lines are trimmed.
====================================================================================================
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=>
    => "
        abc


        "

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

<Function expression="true">
    <Function expression="true">
        <String value="abc

"/>
    </Function>
</Function>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
